<h1>MLB Robot Journalism</h1>

<h2>About</h2>
<div width=50%>
  <p>
    This is a program that fetches play-by-play data of a game from MLB.com 
    and analyzes the overall trend of the game. Using the analysis, it detects 
    the highlights of the game and generates a short article on the game chosen.
    <br>
    
    <br>
    Written by Sean D Kim from Carnegie Mellon University, under the guidance of 
    Professor Jun-Hwan Lee and Dong-Hwan Kim from Seoul National University. 
    Written in Ruby on Rails. 
    <br>
    
    <br>
    Please choose a date to start. 
  </p>
</div>

<form action='event/select_game'>
  <fieldset>
  <legend>Date</legend>
    <p>Year:
    <select name="year">
      <% [2016, 2015, 2014, 2013].each do |i| %>
        <option><%=i%></option>
      <% end %>
    </select>
    </p>
    <p>Month:
    <select name="month">
    <% (1..12).each do |i| %>
      <option><%=i%></option>
    <% end %>
    </select>
    </p>
    <p>Day:
    <select name="day">
    <% (1..31).each do |i| %>
      <option><%=i%></option>
    <% end %>
    </select>
    </p>
  <input type="submit" value="Proceed">
  </fieldset>
  <br>
  <br>
</form>

